info.headline: Flood Warning issued June 06 at 9:51PM EDT until June 07 at 8:00PM EDT by NWS Melbourne
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Melbourne FL has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Florida... St Johns River Near Astor affecting Volusia and Lake Counties. .Tidal influences will cause river levels to hover around Minor Flood Stage tonight and Wednesday. The river is forecast to fall back to Action Stage by late Wednesday. For the St. Johns River...including Astor...Minor flooding is forecast. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued Wednesday morning by 11 AM EDT. && ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT FROM THIS EVENING TO TOMORROW EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...St Johns River Near Astor. * WHEN...From this evening to tomorrow evening. * IMPACTS...At 2.3 feet, Minor flooding of low lying streets and yards north of Fox Road on Lake County side of Astor, and from River Road northward on Volusia side of river. Water begins to cover docks at South Moon Fish Camp. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 8:30 PM EDT Tuesday the stage was 2.3 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to hover around 2.3 feet tonight and Wednesday, then drop below flood stage by Wednesday evening, and continue to recede to 1.6 feet by Sunday. - Flood stage is 2.3 feet. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood && Fld Observed Forecasts (8 pm) Location Stg Stg Day/Time Wed Thu Fri Sat Sun St Johns River Astor 2.3 2.3 Tue 8 pm 2.3 1.9 1.7 1.6 1.6 &&
